784
00:51:32,673 --> 00:51:34,513
<i>Won't Tony be jealous?</i>

785
00:51:34,759 --> 00:51:39,559
<i>Tony is Tom's horse, and we always
thought they went everywhere together.</i>

786
00:51:40,932 --> 00:51:44,982
<i>There's that fellow Chaplin again,
this time with Adolphe Menjou.</i>

787
00:51:46,437 --> 00:51:49,067
<i>There's Claire Windsor
and Dolores del Rio,</i>

788
00:51:49,190 --> 00:51:51,690
<i>and a very charming Eudora Fletcher</i>

789
00:51:51,984 --> 00:51:56,074
<i>chatting with Hollywood's newest
dancing sensation, James Cagney.</i>

790
00:51:57,323 --> 00:51:59,243
<i>Oh, and what have we here?</i>

791
00:51:59,617 --> 00:52:02,617
<i>Only a beautiful lady
named Carole Lombard.</i>

792
00:52:03,704 --> 00:52:06,374
<i>And there's Dr. Fletcher and Leonard Zelig</i>

793
00:52:06,457 --> 00:52:09,707
<i>hitting a few with Bobby Jones
on Mr. Hearst's golf course.</i>

794
00:52:11,170 --> 00:52:14,307
<i>Unless Leonard can go back
to his old chameleon personality</i>

795
00:52:14,382 --> 00:52:16,092
<i>and turn into a golf pro,</i>

796
00:52:16,175 --> 00:52:18,215
<i>I'd bet my money on Bobby.</i>

797
00:52:18,636 --> 00:52:21,216
<i>But who cares, if they're having fun?</i>

798
00:52:28,729 --> 00:52:31,569
Leonard Zelig, do you want to give
the kids of this country some advice?

799
00:52:32,024 --> 00:52:34,744
I sure do. Kids, you gotta be yourself.

800
00:52:35,528 --> 00:52:37,038
You know, you can't act like anybody else

801
00:52:37,113 --> 00:52:40,073
just because you think that they have
all the answers and you don't.

802
00:52:40,783 --> 00:52:44,163
You have to be your own man and learn
to speak up and say what's on your mind.

803
00:52:44,871 --> 00:52:47,121
Now, maybe they're not free
to do that in foreign countries,

804
00:52:47,206 --> 00:52:48,876
but that's the American way.

805
00:52:49,500 --> 00:52:52,960
And you can take it from me, because I
used to be a member of the reptile family,

806
00:52:53,045 --> 00:52:54,835
but I'm not anymore.

807
00:53:00,261 --> 00:53:04,221
MAN: (SINGING)
<i>I'm sittin' on top of the world</i>

